OL,6,FIt is no exaggeration to say that HM  
OL,7,FQueen Elizabeth II was the first      
OL,8,Fmonarch of the television age.        
OL,10,FIn 1952 television in Britain was     
OL,11,Falready setting out on the path which 
OL,12,Fwould rapidly turn it from a scientific
OL,13,Fwonder or distraction for a minority to
OL,14,Fa vital part of everyday life.        
OL,16,FWhen George VI died, only three       
OL,17,Ftransmitters were in service  covering
OL,18,FLondon, the Midlands and much of      
OL,19,Fnorthern England.                     
OL,3,CThe role of big Royal occasions in the
OL,4,Cdevelopment of television             
OL,22,                                  G1/10
