PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F346A1664222673
OL,6,FThe transmitter covering central      
OL,7,FScotland was weeks away from opening. 
OL,8,FSpecial arrangements were put in place
OL,9,Fso if could temporarily come into     
OL,10,Foperation to broadcast the King's     
OL,11,Ffuneral but it is unclear just how many
OL,12,Faround Glasgow and Edinburgh were     
OL,13,Factually able to watch.               
OL,15,FHowever, it was the decision to       
OL,16,Fbroadcast the Coronation in 1953 which
OL,17,Ftruly marked the start of the         
OL,18,Ftelevision age in Britain. More       
OL,19,Ftransmitters were brought into service
OL,20,Frapidly to try to ensure as many people
OL,21,Fas possible were able to watch.       
OL,3,CThe role of big Royal occasions in the
OL,4,Cdevelopment of television             
OL,22,                                  G2/10
