OL,6,FOf course, there's no doubt television
OL,7,Fwould have gradually taken off in     
OL,8,FBritain as it did in every other      
OL,9,Fcomparable country.                   
OL,11,FWith the BBC at the centre of the     
OL,12,Fsystem it would always be a worthwhile
OL,13,Fendeavour  attempting to make a wide 
OL,14,Frange of programmes including some of 
OL,15,Fgenuine distinction and importance.   
OL,17,FBut without the booster rocket of the 
OL,18,FCoronation the path may have been     
OL,19,Fdifferent.                            
OL,3,CThe role of big Royal occasions in the
OL,4,Cdevelopment of television             
OL,22,                                  G5/10
