OL,6,FCoronation Day itself provided the    
OL,7,Fnovelty of almost uninterrupted viewing
OL,8,Ffrom mid-morning until late evening.  
OL,10,FInterestingly Radio Times even billed 
OL,11,Fthe tuning signal  broadcast much    
OL,12,Fearlier than usual  which presumably 
OL,13,Fwas to help with last minute TV       
OL,14,Finstallations.                        
OL,16,FLater on it is interesting to note how
OL,17,Fmany other Royal occasions over the   
OL,18,Fyears were pivotal to the story of    
OL,19,Ftelevision's development.             
OL,3,CThe role of big Royal occasions in the
OL,4,Cdevelopment of television             
